        <p>
            William Shakespeare was a renowned English playwright and poet, widely regarded as one of the greatest writers in the English language. Born in 1564, he penned 38 plays and 154 sonnets, including iconic works like "Romeo and Juliet", "Hamlet" and "Macbeth". His writings continue to captivate audiences with their complex characters, rich language, and timeless themes. Shakespeare's legacy has endured for centuries, influencing literature, theater, and art.
        </p>
